title: New York Firm Recalls Ready-To-Eat Beef and Cheese Pie Products Produced Without Benefit Of Inspection
summary: WASHINGTON, Dec 4, 2012 - Cantina Foods, a Buffalo, N.Y. establishment, is recalling approximately 2,375 pounds of ready-to-eat beef and cheese pie products because they were produced without the benefit of federal inspection, the U.S. Department of Agriculture's Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced...
impacted_products: Cartons containing four clear plastic bags with six 4-oz. "Beef and Cheese Pastellios" in each bag.
